Day 5 – Data Structures & Algorithms (DSA) Learning Outcomes

Topics Covered

* Understood Time Complexity and Space Complexity
* learned to analyze algorithm efficiency using Big-O notation.
* Learned Arrays in Python (Lists), including indexing, traversal, insertion, deletion, searching, and their time complexities.
* Studied Linked Lists, including node structure, advantages, disadvantages, and differences between arrays and linked lists.
* Implemented and understood Stacks (LIFO) using Python lists with operations such as Push, Pop, Peek, and isEmpty.
* Implemented and understood Queues (FIFO) using Python lists and `collections.deque`, including Enqueue, Dequeue, Peek, and their applications.
* Learned Hash Maps (Dictionaries) in Python, including key-value storage, CRUD operations, iteration, hashing concept, and frequency counting applications.
* Studied Trees, including Root, Parent, Child, Leaf Node, Binary Trees, and Binary Search Trees (BST), along with their properties and applications.
* Implemented and compared Searching Algorithms:

  * Linear Search
  * Binary Search
  * Compared their working principles, prerequisites, and time complexities.

* Studied Sorting Algorithms:

  * Bubble Sort
  * Selection Sort
  * Insertion Sort
  * Merge Sort (Concept)
  * Quick Sort (Concept)
* Learned Recursion, including recursive functions, base cases, recursive calls, and implemented recursive solutions for Factorial, Sum of N Numbers, and Fibonacci sequence.

Key Concepts Learned

* Time & Space Complexity Analysis
* Big-O Notation
* Linear vs Hierarchical Data Structures
* LIFO vs FIFO
* Arrays vs Linked Lists
* Binary Tree vs Binary Search Tree
* Linear Search vs Binary Search
* Comparison of Common Sorting Algorithms
* Dictionary Operations
* Recursive Problem Solving using Base Cases

Learning Outcome

Successfully developed a strong foundational understanding of Data Structures and Algorithms (DSA), including algorithm analysis, searching, sorting, recursion, and the implementation of fundamental data structures in Python. Gained hands-on coding experience along with conceptual knowledge required for technical interviews and AI/ML programming fundamentals.

